      "span_text": "Several years ago, Knuiman et al. [CITATION_1] scrutinized 24 studies on the effect of dietary lecithin (ranging from 1 to 54 g per day), in order to establish whether the consumption of lecithin had a more beneficial effect on serum cholesterol levels than equivalent amounts of polyunsaturated triglyceride."
